==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[submergere]]'', from ''[[sub-#Latin|sub-]]'' ("under") + ''[[mergere]]'' ("to plunge").

===Verb===
'''submerge'''
====Intransitive====
# to [[sink]] out of [[sight]].
#:''The submarine '''submerged''' in the water.''

=====Translations=====
*German: [[abtauchen]]
*Japanese: [[沈む]] ([[しずむ]], shizumú)

====Transitive====
# to [[put]] into a [[liquid]]; to [[immerse]]; to [[plunge]] into and keep in.
#:''In films many people are murdered by '''being submerged''' in a swimming pool.''

=====Translations=====
*German: [[untertauchen]]
*Japanese: [[沈める]] ([[しずめる]], shizumerú)

===Derived terms===
*to [[immerse]]
*[[submergence]]
*[[submersion]]